beer.beer_description:
A blend of pale and Vienna malts gives this West Coast IPA a sturdy base and sunny, golden appearance.

As you might expect, there’s plenty of hops on show, with classic US strains (+ a cameo from Citra) joining forces to get the job done.

Expect a flurry of tinned fruit aromas, with lifted notes of crushed pine. To drink, it’s full and fresh, showing more fruit, well-integrated bitterness, and a clean, malty finish.

Malt: Pale Malt, Vienna Malt

Hops: Simcoe, Centennial, Citra, Idaho 7
